**Security Architecture Design:**

**Authentication:**
- JWT access tokens (15-60 minutes expiration)
- Refresh tokens (7-30 days) for persistent sessions
- BCrypt password hashing (rounds: 12)
- Token structure: `{ "sub": user_id, "role": "ADMIN|AGENT|ADJUSTER|VIEWER", "iat": ..., "exp": ... }`

**Authorization (RBAC):**
| Endpoint Pattern | Public | VIEWER | AGENT | ADJUSTER | ADMIN |
|------------------|--------|--------|-------|----------|-------|
| POST /auth/login | Yes | — | — | — | — |
| POST /auth/register | — | — | — | — | Yes |
| GET /users/me | — | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| GET /policies/* | — | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| POST /policies | — | — | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| PUT /policies/* | — | — | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| GET /claims/* | — | — | Yes | Yes | Yes |
| POST /claims | — | — | — | Yes | Yes |
| PUT /claims/* | — | — | — | Yes | Yes |
| POST /payments | — | — | — | Yes | Yes |
| PUT /payments/* | — | — | — | Yes | Yes |
| DELETE /users/* | — | — | — | — | Yes |

**Input Validation & OWASP Mitigation:**
- All request bodies validated via Pydantic schemas
- SQL injection prevented by SQLAlchemy parameterization
- XSS prevented by JSON-only responses (no HTML rendering)
- CORS configured with specific origins (no wildcards in production)
- Rate limiting on authentication endpoints
- Data masking: SSN/TIN show only last 4 digits in all responses

> **Update Todos** Analyze requirements and design architec, Make technology decisions and create tec, Design component boundaries and define p

**Observability Strategy:**

**Logging:**
- structlog with JSON formatting in production, readable format in development
- Log levels: ERROR (failures), WARN (degradation), INFO (business events), DEBUG (troubleshooting)
- NEVER log: passwords, JWT tokens, SSN/TIN full values, payment card details, API keys

**Correlation IDs:**
- Generate UUID for each incoming request via middleware
- Propagate via `X-Correlation-Id` header
- Include in ALL log statements via Python contextvars
- Return correlation ID in response headers for traceability

**Health Checks:**
- **Liveness** — `/health/live` (app is running, simple 200 OK)
- **Readiness** — `/health/ready` (database connectivity, external service status)
- Custom FastAPI health check endpoints with dependency injection

**Metrics:**
- Request count, response time percentiles, error rates by endpoint
- Business metrics: policies created, claims processed, payments completed
- Database connection pool metrics, external integration response times

> **Update Todos** Analyze requirements and design architec, Make technology decisions and create tec, Design component boundaries and define p

**Configuration Management Strategy:**

Following 12-Factor App principles with Pydantic Settings:

| Variable | Description | Default | Required |
|----------|-------------|---------|----------|
| DATABASE_URL | Database connection string | sqlite+aiosqlite:///./dev.db | Yes |
| JWT_SECRET_KEY | JWT signing key (256-bit) | MUST be set in prod | Yes |
| JWT_ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES | Token lifetime | 60 | No |
| JWT_REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRE_DAYS | Refresh token lifetime | 30 | No |
| CORS_ORIGINS | Allowed CORS origins | ["http://localhost:3000"] | No |
| LOG_LEVEL | Logging level | INFO | No |
| ENVIRONMENT | Environment profile | development | No |
| ENCRYPTION_KEY | Data encryption key (Fernet) | MUST be set in prod | Yes |
| STRIPE_SECRET_KEY | Stripe API secret | MUST be set for payments | Conditional |
| STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET | Stripe webhook secret | MUST be set for payments | Conditional |

**Environment Profiles:**
- **Development** — aiosqlite, detailed logging, relaxed CORS, mock external services
- **Production** — PostgreSQL, JSON logging, restricted CORS, real integrations

